":"heading"},{"data":{"text":"Introduction"},"id":"84e81028-b682-40bf-bf8d-ad57d1cf1ef2","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["<em>Editor&#39;s Note: This review has been removed from our side-by-side comparison because it no longer ranks as a top 10 product. The original review is below, but check out our current top 10 about <a href=\"/money/small-business\">online file sharing services here</a>.</em>","SendThisFile is an <a href=\"/money/small-business\">online file sharing service</a> with the purpose in the name – sharing files. Most email providers limit the size of an attached file to between 20MB and 40MB. While this is big enough to send your boss a word document, many files are too big. SendThisFile allows you to share large files because there is no limit to file size. File sharing is done in two ways – an email plugin or a share link. The email plugin seamlessly integrates with your email so that you can attach any file. The share link creates a URL that allows recipients to download the file from any web browser. All you have to do is email the URL.","SendThisFile&#39;s subscription plans provide 500GB of online storage and 500GB of monthly bandwidth for sharing files. If you need to share large files often, 500GB of bandwidth is not a lot. If you create a share link for a 5GB video and it&#39;s downloaded five times, then you&#39;ve used 30GB of bandwidth – 5GB for the initial upload and 25GB for the five downloads. The best file sharing websites either don&#39;t limit your bandwidth or provide 6TB or more each month.","Once you look beyond the basic file sharing, SendThisFile doesn&#39;t provide many features that compare to the best file sharing sites. You can&#39;t create share folders for online collaborations or sync folders for easy access to your files across all your devices. In addition, there aren&#39;t mobile apps, which means you can&#39;t share large files on the go.","For secure file sharing, SendThisFile uses 128-bit, end-to-end encryption. While this protects your files from hackers, it isn&#39;t as good as the industry-standard, 256-bit AES encryption. In addition, it lacks firewall protection, virus scanners and a remote-wipe tool. The only security feature that it has is the ability to password protect the share links. Only recipients who receive the password can download the file. The passwords are never saved to the servers or shared by the service, so you have to communicate it to the recipient.","SendThisFile&#39;s file tracking features are slim because it doesn&#39;t have share folders. As such, it doesn&#39;t maintain any multiple versions of a file. You only have the one file that you uploaded to your account. And if you edit the file, you have to upload it again. The changes won&#39;t automatically update to your account when you hit save. You can track a file&#39;s history with an audit log. You can also require that recipients verify their identity before downloading a file. This is important for tracking who has downloaded files in the audit log."]},"id":"367b10f0-fc24-4f7e-9736-fed4d5033a3c","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"8b4dee42-9cce-4ee3-8b68-7bd44c312c54","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["SendThisFile is an online file sharing site that allows you to share large files easily through email plugins and share links. However, it doesn&#39;t have a lot of monthly bandwidth for sharing files and lacks most of the features you&#39;d expect with a file sharing service, like share folders, device syncing, mobile apps and file versioning."]},"id":"2cfbfec1-9466-4681-85ac-5bfdf699effc","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"product_review_page_53537","url":"/sendthisfile-review","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"jeph-preece","url":"/author/jeph-preece","dateCreated":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","name":"Jeph Preece","dateModified":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","id":"UEqrRM5xmXnCHCjkbS6o5e","dateImported":null,"site":"toptenreviews"}],"territories":["US","GB"],"companies":[],